    "# DCMD pilot plant model for the monovalent stream\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook contains the DCMD simulation of the monovalent stream model used for the V2 report.  \n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "## What this notebook does\n",
    "It models a **single-pass DCMD module** for an NaCl-water brine stream and predicts:\n",
    "\n",
    "- brine outlet flowrate\n",
    "- brine outlet NaCl concentration\n",
    "- brine outlet temperature\n",
    "- distillate production rate\n",
    "- permeate outlet temperature\n",
    "- average membrane flux\n",
    "- water recovery per pass\n",
    "\n",
    "It also creates segment-by-segment tables for all 50 segments of the module so the calculation can be checked more easily.\n",
    "\n",
    "## How the model is organised\n",
    "1. **Inputs and design assumptions**  \n",
    "   Defines the feed stream and the chosen membrane/module design values.\n",
    "\n",
    "2. **Property correlations**  \n",
    "   Provides simplified property functions for NaCl brine and water.\n",
    "\n",
    "3. **DCMD module model**  \n",
    "   Solves coupled brine-side and permeate-side balances across the membrane.\n",
    "\n",
    "4. **Tables and CSV export**  \n",
    "   Displays the final results and saves the full segment tables for checking.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Important modelling notes\n",
    "- The model is steady state.\n",
    "- The feed is treated as an NaCl-water system only.\n",
    "- The module is divided into 50 equal segments along a 1 m channel.\n",
    "- Brine is solved from segment 1 to segment 50.\n",
    "- Permeate is solved in the opposite direction because the module is counter-current (from segment 50 to segment 1).\n",
    "- The temperature profiles are converged using Gauss-Seidel style iteration with under-relaxation.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Reading the segment numbering\n",
    "- **Segment 1** is where the hot brine enters and the warm permeate leaves.\n",
    "- **Segment 50** is where the cold permeate enters and the concentrated brine leaves."
   ]
