    "## Notes on the DCMD module solution\n",
    "\n",
    "This is the core of the notebook.\n",
    "\n",
    "### What is being solved\n",
    "The module is split into **50 equal axial segments**.  \n",
    "For each segment, the model updates:\n",
    "\n",
    "- brine flowrate\n",
    "- brine concentration\n",
    "- brine temperature\n",
    "- permeate flowrate\n",
    "- permeate temperature\n",
    "- local flux\n",
    "- local water transfer\n",
    "\n",
    "### Why the permeate loop is iterative\n",
    "The brine side is solved forwards, but the permeate side is solved backwards because the module is counter-current.  \n",
    "That means the permeate temperature profile is not known at the start, so the code guesses it and improves the guess until the whole profile stops changing.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Convergence method\n",
    "A simple **Gauss-Seidel style iteration** with **under-relaxation** is used:\n",
    "- the model calculates a new permeate temperature profile\n",
    "- only part of that new profile is accepted each iteration\n",
    "- the process repeats until the profile change is small enough\n",
    "\n",
    "This is why the code reports the number of iterations at the end."
   ]
